    • Field Detail

      • m_experiments

        public java.util.List<Experiment> m_experiments
        The list of experiments in this table. Note that we use a list, and not a set, as we need the experiments to be enumerated in the same order every time. Otherwise, the n-th "row" of the table would not always refer to the same data point.

      • getEntries

        public java.util.List<ca.uqac.lif.mtnp.table.TableEntry> getEntries(boolean temporary,
                                                                    Experiment e,
                                                                    int row_start,
                                                                    java.lang.String... dimensions)
        Expands an experiment into multiple table entries, if the experiment has parameters whose value is a list instead of a scalar value. This allows a single experiment to define multiple data points.
        Parameters:
        temporary - Set to true if the table is a temporary table, i.e. a table that is not associated with the lab
        e - The experiment
        row_start - Unused; will likely be deprecated in a future version
        dimensions - The columns to consider when expanding
        Returns:
        A list of table entries corresponding to the data points in the experiment
